tool.name: CreateLiDARProducts

param.name: Input_LAS_Files
param.dialogReference: Input the source .las and/or .zlas files. Note: only .las data can be updated, so the reclassification options are not available when .zlas files are included in the input.

param.name: Output_Folder
param.dialogReference: The output folder where the LiDAR products will be created.

param.name: Output_Name
param.dialogReference: The name used as the file name for output products.

param.name: LAS_File_Projection
param.dialogReference: The coordinate system for the input .las and/or .zlas files.

param.name: Extent_Polygon
param.dialogReference: A polygon feature layer representing one or more areas of interest that will be used to limit the spatial extent of the analysis.

param.name: create_dem
param.dialogReference: Create a Digital Elevation Model from the LiDAR data.

param.name: Create_Slope
param.dialogReference: Create a slope model from the calculated DEM.

param.name: Create_Hillshade
param.dialogReference: Create a hillshade model from the calculated DEM.

param.name: Create_Intensity
param.dialogReference: Create an intensity surface model from the LiDAR data.

param.name: Extract_LiDAR_Polygons
param.dialogReference: Extract selected LiDAR class codes as polygons.

tool.summary: Create LiDAR products from las and zlas files.
